  "prompt": "Do the construction companies offer training to their freshers?",
  "response": "Yes, many construction companies offer training programs for their freshers. These programs are designed to help new employees develop the skills and knowledge necessary for their roles within the company. Training can include a mix of on-the-job training, classroom instruction, safety training, mentorship, and sometimes even certification courses. The aim is to ensure that new hires are well-prepared to contribute effectively to projects and to foster their professional growth in the construction industry.",
